  "text": "We were able to adjust for a number of important possible confounders, but unmeasured confounders might still exist. It has been brought forward that adjustment or even stratification of birth weight by gestational age may introduce bias from such unknown confounders (collider bias) [CITATION_1] . It seems, however, not likely that such bias had a major impact on our findings, because adjustment for gestational age did not change the results substantially.",
